reviews.text: Good medical devices and good doctors. I had a good experience for my case. I am grateful

One of the well-equipped and well-known public hospital in Hong Kong island near Pokfulam. Many famous doctors and specialists. But you must get a referral letter from a doctor before you go there and make appointment for consultation. 💪💪💪

Incredibly dedicated staff members for leukemia patients, prior, during and after bone marrow transplant. The nurses are hard working, compassionate, always willing to accommodate patients. The oncologists are highly professional, attentionate, willing to answer all questions and to give detailed explanations. 
I am deeply touched by the beauty of this hospital's indoor environment, just as much as the outdoor one!
The best hospital in Hong Kong

Went to check up with the wife, not only am I not allow to sit with her, I got kicked out of the next hall where there's clearly empty seats. There were minimal instructions and staffs are rude.

Let me clarify, when we walked in, the lady just gestured for my wife to sit. When I tried to sit next to her, the lady said I can't. But she stops there. If she had told me I can wait on the side or give explanations, it would be fine. I can't comment on the care or the experience of my wife, but as a husband - you are given the impression that you are not welcomed.

reviews.text: 2O19年7月22日星期一我很辛苦幫助帶阿貞丈夫之前上午9時正一起去將軍澳醫院覆診看眼科醫生之後趕時間去瑪麗醫院中午12時正病房探病看我的聾啞朋友不要傷心
我很忙碌很久沒有看facebooK香港肝臟移㨁協康會和瑪麗醫院上網。每逢星期三我練習跳舞太累了。
朗賢前三年到瑪麗醫院做磁力共振。
地方寬敞明亮，醫療設備先進
